Description. Male ( FSCA from Trinidad , Arena Forest Reserve, 01.07.1999 ). Total length: 3.70 . Carapace orange, variegated with dark brown on borders, 1.88 long, 1.44 wide, 1.05 high (
Fig. 108
). Ocular quadrangle 1.08 long. Anterior eye row 1.23 wide and posterior 1.10 wide. Palp yellow (
Figs 113‒114
); both RvTA and ITA poorly developed; embolar base stout bearing the sperm duct opening; DEA tip triangular. Legs 1423 , I orange, II and III light yellow, IV yellow. Dark longitudinal stripes only on legs I and IV (
Figs 108‒110
). Length of femur: I 1.67 , II 0.99 , III 0.93 , IV 1.37 ; patella + tibia: I 2.44 , II 1.28 , III 1.17 , IV 1.66 ; metatarsus + tarsus: I 2.55 , II 1.01 , III 1.09 , IV 1.40 . Spination on ventral tibia I: 2 - 2 - 2 - 2 . Abdomen cream-colored, dorsally with a brown round spot (
Fig. 108
); ventrally cream-colored.

